alwaysApply: true
---
#Apply JSDoc-style documentation to the frontend.

Add JSDoc to exported functions, custom hooks, API client functions, shared utilities, context providers, reducers, complex components, and functions with side effects.

Do not add JSDoc to trivial local handlers, obvious presentational components, or one-line helpers.

For TypeScript, do not repeat obvious type information already present in the function signature.

Comments should explain intent, invariants, side effects, architecture boundaries, or security constraints. Do not add comments that merely restate the code.